.container
  .row
    %h1.text-center List Uniquifier
    .lead
      De-duplicate your lists and and identify items they have in common . e.g.
    .lead
      %ul
        %li Inputs: List A = [w, w, x, y, z] List B = [a, b, y, z]
    .lead Outputs
    %ul
      %li List A will be replaced with a unique version [w, x, y, z], same with List B
      %li List A-unique: [w, x]
      %li Shared Items: [y, z]
      %li List B-unique: [a, b]
    .lead
      No data is sent to the server.  All the comparison happens in your own browser.  Go forth and compare.
    .lead.strong
      Note - Items can be separated with comma or separate line (or mixed)
  .row
    .col-md-6
      %h2
        List A
      #list-a-items
      %textarea.form-control{rows: 7, id: "textarea-list-a"}
        w, w, x, y, z

    .col-md-6
      %h2
        List B
      #list-b-items
      %textarea.form-control{rows: 7, id: "textarea-list-b"}
        a, b, y, z
.contain-fluid
  .row
    .col-lg-12.text-center
      %a.btn.btn-lg.btn-success{id: "btnCompare" } Compare
      %a.btn.btn-lg.btn-default{id: "btnClear"} Clear all
.contain-fluid
  .row
    .col-md-4
      %h2 List A uniques
      #list-a-unique-items
      %textarea.form-control{rows: 7, id: "textarea-list-a-unique"}

    .col-md-4
      %h2 List A/B Shared
      #list-ab-shared
      %textarea.form-control{rows: 7, id: "textarea-list-shared"}

    .col-md-4
      %h2 List B uniques
      #list-b-unique-items
      %textarea.form-control{rows: 7, id: "textarea-list-b-unique"}
